The boot is stuck at SMARTDRV. I've simplified both AUTOEXEC.BAT and CONFIG.SYS. Need to restart QEMU to apply changes.

{
  "analysis": "SMARTDRV.EXE is hanging the boot process. I've now stripped it from both AUTOEXEC.BAT and CONFIG.SYS. Also removed HIMEM.SYS and other potentially problematic drivers. Need to restart QEMU with the clean image.",
  "plan": "Kill current QEMU, restart, and monitor the boot through VGA text memory reading.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "kill $(pgrep qemu-system) 2>/dev/null; sleep 2; rm -f /tmp/qemu-monitor.sock\n",
      "duration": 5.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "nohup qemu-system-i386 -m 32 -hda /app/isos/win311.img -snapshot -vnc :1 -monitor unix:/tmp/qemu-monitor.sock,server,nowait -vga cirrus -net nic,model=ne2k_isa -net user -boot c > /tmp/qemu.log 2>&1 &\necho \"PID: $!\"\n",
      "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "sleep 10 && python3 /tmp/read_vga.py\n",
      "duration": 15.0
    }
  ],
  "task_complete": false
}
